<br>
The problem is, the knights have to be close in tanking ability to warriors or we are just a waist of a group slot. I've seen people saying it on this thread, and knights have know it for a long time, but defense doesn't stack. Either you are good enough to tank, or you aren't. That is the basic problem.<br>
<br>
The fact that this game hes devolved (right from the get go) into encounters of multiple people handling a single target at a time, with one person designated to take all melee damage, is the big problem. That situation doesn't allow melee defense to stack.<br>
<br>
Should warriors be better defensively than paladins and shadow knights? Yes, but by a small margin. I would argue that if AC was fixed so that warriors had an appreciable advantage from higher AC and hp, followed closely by the knights, then a nice gap between the knights and the damage dealing melee, the problem would be solved. None of the damage dealing melee classes have a problem, damage output is one of the major keys to the game, and you can never have too much. (and monks tank just too damn well)<br>
<br>
